LogFile.FinalText: Some people would say that men and women speak a different language. If a man in a relationship says that he does not want to talk about his problems, the typical woman would feel that he is shutting her out from his world. If the woman says to him that she does not want to talk to him about her problems, most men would assume that she does not have a need to talk about them. These misunderstandings give cause to fights. When big fights arise, women and men also reacts differently. New research shows that many women cry when they get upset. In such situation, frightened men choose to run away and they may also feel helpless. In stead of crying, the angry man uses harsh words. In spite of these different reactions, most men and women manage to live peacefully together and we probably could not live without each other.
